OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Mon 6 Jul to Wed 15 Jul
OL,6,FHigh pressure will dominate across
OL,7,FEngland and Wales into next week,
OL,8,Flikely extending its influence across
OL,9,Fmore on the northern UK with time.
OL,10,FThis will bring dry and warm
OL,11,Fconditions with plenty of sunshine for
OL,12,Fmost. Scotland and Northern Ireland
OL,13,Fwill probably see more cloud at first,
OL,14,Fwith periods of rain at times. Through
OL,15,Fnext week though the high pressure may
OL,16,Fextend northwards to bring periods of
OL,17,Fdrier and warmer weather to Scotland
OL,18,Fand Northern Ireland. Winds will be
OL,19,Flight to moderate for most, though
OL,20,Fstronger around northern hills and
OL,21,Fcoasts near low pressure systems.
OL,22,FTemperatures becoming widely warm,
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fperhaps locally hot in parts of the
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fsoutheast, although not as hot nor
OL,25,Fhumid as seen in the past week.
